The 5th and final day of the Icasa public hearings will see SuperSport give their presentation. Editor's note: This livestream was stopped due to poor sound quality. CENTURION - The fifth and final day of Icasa’s Public Hearings into its Draft Sports Broadcasting Service Amendment Regulations saw SuperSport give their presentation. Earlier on Friday, Kwesé TV gave their presentation at the public hearings. WATCH: Khoza briefs media on PSL issues One of the big talking points at the hearings is the capacity broadcasters have to televise sport. Federations point to the hours of exposure received from pay-TV compared to free-to-air as the reason they are happy with Icasa’s current regulations, even if it restricts the amount of sport available to all.